---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  locale="en"
  title="Privacy Policy | Hooosberg"
  description="Privacy policy for the Hooosberg website, including hosting logs, consent-based analytics, and visitor rights."
  canonicalPath="/en/privacy"
>
  <section class="legal-page">
    <p class="hero-kicker">Legal</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-page__updated">Last updated: 2026-06-21</p>

    <p>
      hooosberg.com is the public website for Hooosberg. It publishes indie products, build diaries, AI tool notes, courses, and contact links.
      This policy explains what information may be processed when the website operates.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we may process</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Access logs: Cloudflare and hosting infrastructure may process IP address, requested URL, User-Agent, timestamp, and security-event data for delivery, security, and troubleshooting.</li>
      <li>Local preferences: the site stores language, theme, and analytics consent choices in your browser.</li>
      <li>Contact information: if you email us or contact us through an external platform, we receive the content and contact details you choose to send.</li>
      <li>Analytics: Google Analytics loads only after you consent, so we can understand traffic and improve the website.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use information</h2>
    <p>
      We use information to operate and protect the site, understand content performance, answer messages, and improve product pages and build notes.
      We do not sell personal information, and this website does not run account or payment systems.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      The site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages and may use Google Analytics after consent. External links may take you to GitHub, YouTube, X, Bilibili,
      Telegram, the App Store, or other third-party services governed by their own policies.
    </p>

    <h2>EEA, UK, Switzerland, and similar regions</h2>
    <p>
      For visitors in regions with GDPR-style data protection rules, non-essential analytics loads only after consent.
      You may withdraw consent in your browser and contact us to request access, deletion, correction, or restriction of information related to you.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy questions can be sent to <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:zikedece@proton.me">zikedece@proton.me</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
